From jbrandt J Brandt Subject Beta Testers Wanted for Graphics Libraries Visual Numerics formerly IMSL and Precision Visuals is in the process of securing sites for beta testing X Exponent Graphics and C Exponent Graphics Both X Exponent Graphics and C Exponent Graphics are products The beta period is from April through June The platform is running under OS with ansi C The media will be sent on DAT cartridge Here are some of the key facts about the two X Exponent Graphics key facts Complete collection of high level and application plot types available through a large collection of X Cstom widget for OSF Motif Built in interactive GUI for plot Easily implemented callbacks for customized application XEG being built on the Xt Toolkit provides the user a widget library that conforms to the expected syntax and standards familar to X XEG will also be sold as a bundle with Visual Edge's UIM X This will enable user to use a GUI builder to create the graphical layout of an C Exponent Graphics key facts Written in C for C application programmers The library is written in C and the programming interface conforms to C standards taking advantage fo the most desirable features of Build in GUI for interactive plot Through mouse interaction the user has complete interactive graph output control with over graphics attributes for plot Large collection of high level application functions for two call graph A wide variety of and plot types are available with minimal programming User ability to interrupt and control the X By controlling the X event loop when the user use the mouse to manipulate the plot the user can allow CEG to control the event loop or the user can control the event If anyone is interested in beta testing either of the products please contact Wendy Hou at Visual Numerics via email at or call Jaclyn Brandt jbrandt